gt:
We can start by drawing a diagram of the routes that each of them took: [asy]
size(150);
draw((0,0)--(0,9)--(12,9)--cycle,linewidth(1));
label("9",(0,4.5),W);
label("12",(6,9),N);
label("15",(6,4.5),SE);
[/asy] The two routes form a 9-12-15 right triangle.  Kelly drove for $9+12=21$ miles at a rate of 42 miles per hour, so she drove for $21/42=.5$ hours which equals 30 minutes.  Brenda drove for 15 miles at an average rate of 45 miles per hour, so she drove for $15/45\cdot 60=20$ minutes.  Thus, Brenda arrived $30-20=\boxed{10}$ minutes earlier than Kelly.

